 {"id":"asupersync-t613","title":"Add cardinality limits and custom exporters for OTel metrics","description":"## Overview

Enhance OpenTelemetry metrics with cardinality limits to prevent explosion and support for custom exporters.

## Requirements

### Cardinality Limits
Prevent metric explosion from high-cardinality labels:

```rust
pub struct MetricsConfig {
    /// Maximum unique label combinations per metric.
    pub max_cardinality: usize,  // Default: 1000

    /// What to do when cardinality limit reached.
    pub overflow_strategy: CardinalityOverflow,

    /// Labels to always drop (e.g., request_id).
    pub drop_labels: Vec<String>,
}

pub enum CardinalityOverflow {
    /// Stop recording new label combinations.
    Drop,

    /// Aggregate into 'other' bucket.
    Aggregate,

    /// Log warning and continue.
    Warn,
}

impl OtelMetrics {
    fn record_with_cardinality_check(&self, metric: &str, labels: &[KeyValue]) {
        if self.cardinality_tracker.would_exceed(metric, labels) {
            match self.config.overflow_strategy {
                CardinalityOverflow::Drop => return,
                CardinalityOverflow::Aggregate => {
                    // Replace high-cardinality labels with 'other'
                }
                CardinalityOverflow::Warn => {
                    tracing::warn!("Cardinality limit reached for {}", metric);
                }
            }
        }
        // Record metric
    }
}
```

### Custom Exporters
Support exporters beyond Prometheus:

```rust
pub trait MetricsExporter: Send + Sync {
    fn export(&self, metrics: &MetricsSnapshot) -> Result<(), ExportError>;
    fn flush(&self) -> Result<(), ExportError>;
}

// Built-in exporters
pub struct PrometheusExporter { ... }
pub struct OtlpExporter { ... }
pub struct StdoutExporter { ... }  // For debugging
pub struct NullExporter { ... }    // For testing

// Multiple exporters
pub struct MultiExporter {
    exporters: Vec<Box<dyn MetricsExporter>>,
}
```

### Metric Sampling
For high-frequency metrics:

```rust
pub struct SamplingConfig {
    /// Sample rate (0.0-1.0). 1.0 = record all.
    pub sample_rate: f64,

    /// Metrics to sample (others recorded fully).
    pub sampled_metrics: Vec<String>,
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
1. Configurable cardinality limits
2. Overflow strategies (drop, aggregate, warn)
3. Custom exporter trait
4. Built-in stdout exporter for debugging
5. Multi-exporter support
6. Sampling for high-frequency metrics

