-{"id":"asupersync-tibn","title":"[EPIC-INFRA] Enhanced Cancel Reason Attribution","description":"## Overview

Enhance the cancellation system to provide detailed attribution for why a task was cancelled, including the originating region, time, and cause chain.

## Strategic Value

**Problem Solved**: When a task is cancelled, users often ask "why?". Current cancellation reasons are coarse (User, Deadline, Parent). Enhanced attribution provides the full story.

**Debugging Value**: Knowing that a task was cancelled due to a deadline in a parent region 3 levels up, 500ms ago, is much more actionable than just "cancelled".

**Production Observability**: In production, understanding cancellation patterns helps identify misconfigured timeouts, overloaded services, and resource contention.

## Design

### Enhanced CancelReason
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct CancelReason {
    /// Primary cause category
    pub kind: CancelKind,
    /// Region that initiated cancellation
    pub origin_region: RegionId,
    /// Task that initiated (if applicable)
    pub origin_task: Option<TaskId>,
    /// Timestamp of cancellation request
    pub timestamp: Instant,
    /// Human-readable message
    pub message: Option<String>,
    /// Cause chain (if propagated from parent)
    pub cause: Option<Box<CancelReason>>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum CancelKind {
    /// User explicitly requested cancellation
    User,
    /// Deadline/timeout expired
    Deadline,
    /// Poll quota exhausted
    PollQuota,
    /// Cost budget exhausted
    CostBudget,
    /// Parent region cancelled
    ParentCancelled,
    /// Shutdown signal received
    Shutdown,
    /// Resource unavailable
    ResourceUnavailable,
}
```

### Attribution Chain
When cancellation propagates from parent to child, the child's CancelReason includes the parent's reason as its cause, forming a chain.

### API Changes
```rust
impl Cx {
    /// Cancel with detailed reason
    pub fn cancel_with(&self, kind: CancelKind, message: impl Into<String>);

    /// Get detailed cancellation reason if cancelled
    pub fn cancel_reason(&self) -> Option<&CancelReason>;

    /// Get the full cause chain
    pub fn cancel_chain(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = &CancelReason>;
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. CancelReason includes origin region, task, timestamp
2. Cause chain preserved through propagation
3. All CancelKind variants documented
4. Tracing integration emits attribution on cancel
5. No performance regression (attribution is lazy)
6. Backwards compatible with existing code

## Dependencies

- Benefits from tracing integration (Epic #2)
- Used by conformance tests (Epic #9)

## Priority Rationale

